31/05/2010
ANKARA, Turkey -- Media reported on Monday (May 31st) that six Turkish soldiers have been killed and several injured as members of the terrorist Kurdistan Workers' Party (PKK) attacked a navy base in southern Turkey.
The PKK members reportedly fired a rocket propelled grenade at a military vehicle near the base in the Mediterranean port of Iskenderun.
(Anadolu news agency, Reuters, BBC, AP, AFP - 31/05/10)
